  "prompt": "How do I recovery whatsapp messagess?",
  "response": "Recovering deleted WhatsApp messages can vary depending on whether you have backups enabled and which operating system your device uses. Here are the steps for both Android and iOS devices:\n\n### On Android:\n\n#### Recovering via Google Drive Backup:\n1. **Uninstall WhatsApp** from your phone.\n2. **Reinstall WhatsApp** from the Google Play Store.\n3. **Open WhatsApp** and verify your phone number.\n4. When prompted, **tap \"Restore\"** to restore your chats and media from Google Drive.\n\n#### Recovering from a Local Backup:\n1. **Open your file manager app** (this may vary depending on your device).\n2. Navigate to **`WhatsApp/Databases`**. If you're unable to find this folder, it may be on your SD card or within your internal storage.\n3. You will see files named like **`msgstore-YYYY-MM-DD.1.db.crypt12`**. Rename the most recent backup file to **`msgstore.db.crypt12`**.\n4. **Uninstall WhatsApp** from your phone.\n5. **Reinstall WhatsApp** from the Google Play Store.\n6. **Open WhatsApp** and verify your phone number.\n7. When prompted, tap **\"Restore\"** from the local backup.\n\n### On iOS:\n\n#### Recovering via iCloud Backup:\n1. **Uninstall WhatsApp** from your iPhone.\n2. **Reinstall WhatsApp** from the App Store.\n3. **Open WhatsApp** and verify your phone number.\n4. When prompted, tap **\"Restore Chat History\"** to restore your chats and media from your iCloud backup.\n\n#### Recovering without a Backup:\nUnfortunately, if you don't have a backup available on either iCloud or Google Drive, recovering deleted messages becomes very difficult because WhatsApp doesn\u2019t store your messages on their servers after they are delivered. There's no official way to retrieve deleted messages without a prior backup.\n\n### Additional Notes:\n- Always ensure regular backups enabled on WhatsApp settings to avoid losing important messages.\n- Keep your backup frequency set as per your needs (e.g., daily, weekly).\n- Make sure your Google Drive or iCloud has enough storage space for your backups.\n\nIf the above methods do not work, you may want to consider using third-party tools specifically designed for data recovery, but proceed with caution as these tools may not always be reliable or secure.",
